</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Concussion </strong>- A mild traumatic brain injury caused by a blow or jolt to the head, resulting in temporary cognitive impairment.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) </strong>-  A severe head injury characterised by prolonged unconsciousness, memory loss, and cognitive deficits.







